title: Case count by zip code
caption: Profiles of 7-day rolling average of COVID-19 new case counts within 26 March, 2020 and 11 May, 2021 across zip-codes in Austin, TX.
insights: The highest number of cases was recorded in the 78660 zip-code area in January 2021.
There are 2 dominant local peaks observed across most profiles with the first occuring just after the onset of the pandemic and having a steeper ascent compared to the second peak.
The cases dropped significantly between these 2 dominant peaks.
